Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

THE BIG PERF WIN. Replaces the per-pixel 14-22 op multiply in the
RGB565 cmod path with a per-pixel 1-byte LUT lookup on INDEX8 — Cave
Story uses 1-3 distinct cmod tuples (Font foreground colors), so the
LUT cache stays tiny while every glyph draw drops to memcpy-shaped
inner loops.

Renderer (src/graphics/Renderer.{h,cpp}):
  * _cmod_lut_cache (std::unordered_map<Uint32, std::array<Uint8,256>>):
    keyed by (r << 16 | g << 8 | b); value is the 256-byte master-
    palette → master-palette LUT for that cmod tuple.
  * Renderer::_cmod_lut_for(r, g, b): builds the LUT lazily on first
    use (256 weighted-Euclidean nearest-color walks ≈ 7.5 ms once on
    PODP83), returns a stable reference. Special-cases (0,0,0) → master
    index 0 and (255,0,255) → master index 255 so the LUT can never
    re-map non-colorkey pixels into the colorkey slot or vice versa.
  * _blit_indexed_color_mod_black: byte-per-pixel sibling of
    _blit_rgb565_color_mod_black. Writes master_black_idx (=0) for
    every non-colorkey source pixel.
  * _blit_indexed_color_mod: byte-per-pixel sibling of
    _blit_rgb565_color_mod_general. Inner loop is `dp[col] =
    cmod_lut[sp[col]]` plus optional colorkey skip — ~3 ops/pixel vs
    14-22 for the RGB565 multiply path.
  * Renderer::drawSurfaceColorMod: 6-way dispatch. white → drawSurface
    (existing); INDEX8 + black → _blit_indexed_color_mod_black; INDEX8
    + general → _blit_indexed_color_mod with cached LUT; RGB565 + black
    → _blit_rgb565_color_mod_black (existing); RGB565 + general →
    _blit_rgb565_color_mod_general (existing); else → SDL_RenderTexture
    fallback.
  * Diagnostic counters (_color_mod_indexed_black_*, _color_mod_indexed_
    general_*) added to the per-100-flip color/alpha audit block so
    real-HW iter logs report whether the new INDEX8 path engaged.

Font.cpp is unchanged: Surface::loadFromSDLSurface (modified in patch
0073) handles the format choice internally, and Font.cpp's call sites
into drawSurfaceColorMod stay identical.

Out of scope (deferred to wave 17): _blit_indexed_alpha (alpha-mod
INDEX8 fast path). Per spec §2.9, alpha-mod calls in indexed mode fall
through to SDL_RenderTexture which the SDL3 SW renderer registers as
INDEX8-capable (vendor/SDL/src/render/software/SDL_render_sw.c:1214).

